<%-- This is the login page for the Bambi Forest application. --%>
<%-- It includes a form for users to enter their username and password. --%>
<%-- If there is an error, it will be displayed above the form. --%>
<%-- The page is styled with CSS and includes a link to the registration page. --%>
<%-- The neon glow effect is applied to the title. --%>
<%-- The form submits to the /login route with a POST request. --%>
<%-- The socket.io library is included for real-time communication. --%>
<%-- The error message is styled with a background color and text color defined in CSS variables. --%>
<%-- The input fields are required and have labels for accessibility. --%>
<%-- The button submits the form and has a label "Enter Forest". --%>
<%-- The page is responsive and adjusts to different screen sizes. --%>
<%-- The container class centers the content and adds padding. --%>
<%-- The card class styles the form area with a white background and rounded corners. --%>
<%-- The neon-glow class applies a glowing effect to the title. --%>
<%-- The input-container class styles the input fields and labels. --%>
<%-- The error-message class styles the error message with a red background and white text. --%>
<%-- The button is styled with a hover effect and transitions. --%>
<%-- The link to the registration page is styled with a color and hover effect. --%>
<%-- The page is designed to be visually appealing and user-friendly. --%>
<%-- The title "Bambi Forest" is displayed prominently at the top of the page. --%>
<%-- The form includes input fields for username and password, both required. --%>
<%-- The error message is conditionally displayed if there is an error. --%>
<%-- The page includes a link to the registration page for new users. --%>
<%-- The socket.io library is included for real-time communication. --%>
<%-- The page is designed to be visually appealing and user-friendly. --%>
<%-- The title "Bambi Forest" is displayed prominently at the top of the page. --%>
<%-- The form includes input fields for username and password, both required. --%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Bambi Forest - Login</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="neon-glow">Bambi Forest</h1>
    
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Enter the Woodland</h2>
      
      <% if (error) { %>
        <div class="error-message" style="background-color: var(--error-bg); color: var(--error); padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 4px;">
          <%= error %>
        </div>
      <% } %>
      
      <form action="/login" method="POST">
        <div class="input-container">
          <label for="username">Username</label>
          <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>
        </div>
        
        <div class="input-container">
          <label for="password">Password</label>
          <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required>
        </div>
        
        <button type="submit">Enter Forest</button>
      </form>
      
      <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">
        Don't have an account? <a href="/register">Join the Woodland</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <script src="/socket.io/socket.io.js"></script>
</body>
</html>